title: two Duryea cards that have a small variation in the team name
author: timkb

posts.post_title: two Duryea cards that have a small variation in the team name
posts.post_content:
I have two Duryea cards that have a small variation in the team name. One is "Cincinnati" the other is "Cincinnatis" with an "s". I have included the photo of the variation with the "s" ontop of the page from the Photographic Baseball Cards of Goodwin & Co. reference book that I consider the ultimate guide of what is out there. In the book they do not have the variation where "Cincinnati" is used and his name and the team name are cut out of the photo.

I assume the authenticated card is real. Is this a new variation that is just over looked?

[IMG]https://preview.ibb.co/eMwcJG/IMG_20171112_085253.jpg[/IMG]

[IMG]https://image.ibb.co/eS5Xkw/Duryea_Authenticated.jpg[/IMG]
We only pictured pose differences in the book, not name plate differences. Team names with or without an “s” at the end is very common and carries no premium.

Now if Jay offers you $500 bucks for it....   :p

You should know I'm kidding Jay....  :)
